    "vl_rich_text_pIH73W": {
      "type": "vl-rich-text",
      "name": "VL Rich Text",
      "settings": {
        "subheading": "Why We're Showing You Unfiltered Photos",
        "content": "<p>The beauty industry has a problem with honesty. Foundation ads show airbrushed skin on women in their twenties, photographed in controlled studio lighting with professional makeup artists on hand. Then they wonder why real women are disappointed when the product arrives.</p><p>We're doing something different. Every photo on this page is from an actual customer. No filters. No retouching. No professional lighting rigs. Just a phone camera, a mirror, and the truth about how the Vera Lane Tone Adapting Foundation looks on real mature skin.</p><p><strong>Some of these women have rosacea.</strong> Some have deep smile lines. Some have sun damage, age spots, or uneven texture. That's the point. If a foundation can't handle real skin concerns, it doesn't deserve your money.</p>",
        "bg_color": "#ffffff",
        "heading_color": "#000000",
        "text_color": "#333333",
        "link_color": "#5C1A33"
      }
    },
